proper noun.description: A country on the coast of West Africa; population 2,000,000 (estimated 2015); capital, Banjul; languages, English (official), Malinke and other indigenous languages, and Creole.
A river in West Africa that rises near Labé in Guinea and flows for 500 miles (800 km) through Senegal and Gambia to meet the Atlantic Ocean at Banjul.
